@startuml
title PayMate Project: Waterfall Model Application

skinparam activity {
    BackgroundColor #ADD8E6
    BorderColor #4682B4
    ArrowColor #333
    FontName Inter
    FontSize 14
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #F5F5F5
    BorderColor #888
    FontName Inter
    FontSize 12
}

start

:1) Requirements Analysis\nRequirements Gathering;
note right
    - Define all features upfront:
      Login, Signup, User Profile
    - Detail every payment flow:
      UPI, Bank Transfer, QR Scan
    - Specify all Bill Payment categories
    - Script the entire AI Chatbot dialogue
end note

-> 2) System Design\nSystem & UI Design;
note right
    - Create finalized wireframes and
      mockups for every single screen
      (Dashboard, Transfer, Bills, etc.)
    - Design the complete system
      architecture and database schema.
    - No changes allowed after this phase.
end note

-> 3) Implementation\nImplementation (Coding);
note right
    - Build the entire frontend in Next.js.
    - Develop the complete backend API.
    - Integrate with all payment gateways
      (Stripe, PayPal, Razorpay) as per design.
    - Code the Genkit AI flows.
end note

-> 4) Testing\nTesting & QA;
note right
    - The full application is tested only
      after all coding is complete.
    - Bugs found here are difficult and
      costly to fix as they may require
      going back to the design phase.
end note

-> 5) Deployment\nDeployment & Release;
note right
    - The completed application is deployed
      to the production server.
    - The product is released to end-users.
end note

-> 6) Maintenance\nMaintenance;
note right
    - Post-launch support and bug fixes.
    - New features would require starting
      a new waterfall cycle.
end note

stop
@enduml
